# CLAUDE.md — Bookmark Manager API

## Project Overview
<!-- Fill this in -->
This is a REST API for saving, tagging, and searching bookmarks, built with Express and TypeScript.

## Key Commands
- `npm run dev` — Start dev server with hot reload
- `npm run test` — Run tests with Vitest
- `npm run lint` — Type-check with TypeScript

## Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types
- Use Express Router for route organization
- All request bodies must be validated before processing
- Use interfaces for all data shapes (Bookmark, Tag, etc.)
- <!-- Add your own rule -->

## API Conventions
- All endpoints return JSON
- POST returns 201 on success
- Error responses: `{ error: string }`
- List responses: `{ data: T[], count: number }`

## Testing Requirements
- Use Vitest for all tests
- Test files: `*.test.ts` next to source files
- Test the service layer, not Express routes directly
- Mock storage for unit tests

## Do NOT
- Use `any` type
- Allow bookmarks without URL validation
- Skip error handling
